{
  "text": "The top eigenvector recovers the initial group elements up to a global sign, since if v Z 1 is the top eigenvector of Z then so is \u2212v Z 1 . We refer the reader to Section 4 of [CITATION_1] for a detailed explanation of the increased noise robustness the above normalization brings, and its connection to the normalized discrete graph Laplacian.",
  "correct_citation": {
